<br>
Human Bard of Prexus<br>
Neutral Alignment<br>
<br>
The only thing I did not see in quick reading is the use of stun when I was a cleric.  I almost always had the two divines and the lower level root and stun in four of my spots.  Not everyone may agree, but root and stun were quick casting and helped me a bunch in dungeons.  Sometimes I even had the two lowest level stuns up.  Anyway I hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ualainifv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AlainiFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/17/02 1:01:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics of Norrath, lend me your ears! :-)</span><hr size=1> 1. What race are you? - Halfling - Short and Cute!<br>
